@startuml c4-jotp-07b-timer-scheduling
title JOTP - Timer Scheduling & Delivery Sequence

participant "Caller\nProcess" as Caller
participant "ProcTimer" as Timer
participant "ScheduledExecutor\nService" as Scheduler
participant "Target\nMailbox" as Mailbox
participant "Target\nProcess" as Target

Caller ->> Timer: send_after(delay, target, msg)
activate Timer

Timer ->> Timer: create TimerTask\nwith message copy

Timer ->> Scheduler: schedule(task, delay, unit)
activate Scheduler
note over Scheduler
  Schedules on background
  executor thread pool
end note

Timer -->> Caller: TimerRef(id)
deactivate Timer

note over Scheduler
  Waiting...
  delay expires
end note

Scheduler ->> Mailbox: enqueue(message)
activate Mailbox

Mailbox ->> Target: message available
activate Target

Target ->> Target: dequeue from mailbox
note over Target
  Process continues
  handling messages
  in FIFO order
end note

Target ->> Target: handle(state, timedMessage)

Target -->> Target: newState
deactivate Target
deactivate Mailbox
deactivate Scheduler

note over Target
  Timed message processed
  like any other message
end note

alt Cancel Before Delivery
  Caller ->> Timer: cancel(timerRef)
  activate Timer
  Timer ->> Scheduler: cancel(future)
  Scheduler -->> Timer: cancelled
  deactivate Timer
  note over Scheduler
    Task never executes
    Message never sent
  end note
end

@enduml
